com.jnape.palatable.lambda.traversable

Class LambdaIterable<A>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.jnape.palatable.lambda.traversable.LambdaIterable<A>
  • Type Parameters:
    A - the Iterable element type
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Applicative<A,LambdaIterable>, Functor<A,LambdaIterable>, Monad<A,LambdaIterable>, Traversable<A,LambdaIterable>

    public final class LambdaIterable<A>
extends Object
implements Monad<A,LambdaIterable>, Traversable<A,LambdaIterable>
    Wrap an Iterable in a Traversable such that Traversable.traverse(Function, Function) applies its computation against each element of the wrapped Iterable. Returns the result of pure if the wrapped Iterable is empty.

      • zip

        public <B> LambdaIterable<B> zip(Applicative<Function<? super A,? extends B>,LambdaIterable> appFn)
        Given another instance of this applicative over a mapping function, "zip" the two instances together using whatever application semantics the current applicative supports.

        In this case, calculate the cartesian product of applications of all functions in appFn to all values wrapped by this LambdaIterable.
